&lt;pre&gt;I was about to LGTM this, noting that you've done a great job with test
coverage, and we've given over a month for the CSSWG to come to a
conclusion but not seen much movement.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

But then I noticed that 16 hours ago, a Firefox engineer has chimed in on
the CSSWG thread
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/12376#issuecomment-3135649756"&gt;https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/12376#issuecomment-3135649756&lt;/a&gt;&gt;,
and sounds interested in collaborating toward interop on this issue.

I don't think we should hold up this intent much longer, but let's take
advantage of this to try to get more signals from Firefox. I'll add my
thoughts to that thread to try to help things along.

