&lt;span class="subject"&gt;&lt;a href="/search?l=blink-dev@chromium.org&amp;q=subject:%22%5C%5Bblink%5C-dev%5C%5D+Intent+to+Prototype%5C%3A+Support+slotting+option+elements+in+select+elements%22&amp;o=newest" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;span itemprop="name"&gt;[blink-dev] Intent to Prototype: Support slotting option elements in select elements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p class="darkgray font13"&gt;
&lt;span class="sender pipe"&gt;&lt;a href="/search?l=blink-dev@chromium.org&amp;q=from:%22Joey+Arhar%22" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"&gt;&lt;span itemprop="name"&gt;Joey Arhar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="date"&gt;&lt;a href="/search?l=blink-dev@chromium.org&amp;q=date:20250806" rel="nofollow"&gt;Wed, 06 Aug 2025 12:33:37 -0700&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div itemprop="articleBody" class="msgBody"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;Contact emailsjar...@chromium.org

Explainer&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/whatwg/html/issues/11535"&gt;https://github.com/whatwg/html/issues/11535&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

SpecificationNone

Summary

This feature makes the select element look in its flat tree for option
elements rather than just looking at its normal DOM descendants. This way,
web components can use select elements in their shadow DOM and users of the
web component can provide option elements. Here is an example:
&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/whatwg/html/issues/11535"&gt;https://github.com/whatwg/html/issues/11535&lt;/a&gt;


Blink componentBlink&gt;DOM
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://issues.chromium.org/issues?q=customfield1222907:%22Blink%3EDOM%22"&gt;https://issues.chromium.org/issues?q=customfield1222907:%22Blink%3EDOM%22&lt;/a&gt;&gt;

Motivation

Without this feature, web component authors have to rebuild their own
select components rather than using customizable select.
&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/whatwg/html/issues/11535#issuecomment-3155754832"&gt;https://github.com/whatwg/html/issues/11535#issuecomment-3155754832&lt;/a&gt;


Initial public proposal&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/whatwg/html/issues/11535"&gt;https://github.com/whatwg/html/issues/11535&lt;/a&gt;

TAG reviewNone

TAG review statusPending

Risks


Interoperability and Compatibility

None


*Gecko*: No signal

*WebKit*: No signal

*Web developers*: No signals

*Other signals*:

WebView application risks

