&gt; Specification &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-view-transitions-2"&gt;https://www.w3.org/TR/css-view-transitions-2&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Summary
&gt;
&gt; Similar to &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/feature/5424291457531904"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/feature/5424291457531904&lt;/a&gt;, which
&gt; inherited animation-delay, this feature adds more animation properties to
&gt; inherit through the view transition pseudo tree based on resolution in
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11546#issuecomment-3005503138:"&gt;https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11546#issuecomment-3005503138:&lt;/a&gt;
&gt; * animation-timing-function * animation-iteration-count *
&gt; animation-direction * animation-play-state
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Blink component Blink&gt;ViewTransitions&gt;SPA
&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://issues.chromium.org/issues?q=customfield1222907:%22Blink%3EViewTransitions%3ESPA%22"&gt;https://issues.chromium.org/issues?q=customfield1222907:%22Blink%3EViewTransitions%3ESPA%22&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
&gt;
&gt; TAG review None
&gt;
&gt; TAG review status Not applicable
&gt;
&gt; Risks
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Interoperability and Compatibility
&gt;
&gt; None
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; *Gecko*: No signal Due to similarity to
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/feature/5424291457531904"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/feature/5424291457531904&lt;/a&gt; (which shipped in
&gt; Firefox), and no concerns raised at CSSWG, I suspect this is positive, but
&gt; no official signals have been filed. Please let me know if you think filing
&gt; a signal is warranted.
&gt;
&gt; *WebKit*: Shipped/Shipping (&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=296174"&gt;https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=296174&lt;/a&gt;)
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; *Web developers*: No signals
&gt;
